						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in a hay-stack.</p>						

						<p>Āravīḍu ruler.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="italic">Bhāva, Pushya,</hi> śu. 11.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to refer to some grant of land by a ruler (name lost) who was described an a Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara and a member of the Āravīḍu family.</p>						

						</summary>
